From: nix-wasm <eric@codebutler.com>
Date: Fri, 20 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wasm: force buffered v9fs I/O (no unbuffered page-pinning)

Phase 1 (per-process memory) capstone fix. With wasm_user_as ON, a 9P write
to the writable /mnt/pc mount (cache=none -> P9L_DIRECT) landed as zeros.
v9fs_file_write_iter routes P9L_DIRECT writes to netfs_unbuffered_write_iter,
which pins the user buffer via netfs_extract_user_iter -> iov_iter_extract_
pages and copies those KERNEL pages -- but each user process now owns a
DISTINCT WebAssembly.Memory the kernel cannot address, so the pin resolves
the shared kernel Memory at the user offset and the data is zero. Page
pinning is fundamentally impossible across separate Memory objects.

Fix: on CONFIG_WASM, never take the unbuffered branch in v9fs_file_{read,
write}_iter; fall through to the cached netfs_file_{read,write}_iter path,
whose copy flows through the host-bridge copy_to/from_user choke point
(patch 0014). Generalizes the cache=loose read mounts to writes too.
CONFIG_WASM-guarded; other arches keep the upstream direct path.

--- a/fs/9p/vfs_file.c	2026-06-19 22:28:30.854982526 -0400
+++ b/fs/9p/vfs_file.c	2026-06-19 22:28:30.866860722 -0400
@@ -362,7 +362,8 @@
 	p9_debug(P9_DEBUG_VFS, "fid %d count %zu offset %lld\n",
 		 fid->fid, iov_iter_count(to), iocb->ki_pos);
 
-	if (fid->mode & P9L_DIRECT)
+	/* CONFIG_WASM: force the cached/buffered path (see v9fs_file_write_iter). */
+	if (!IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_WASM) && (fid->mode & P9L_DIRECT))
 		return netfs_unbuffered_read_iter(iocb, to);
 
 	p9_debug(P9_DEBUG_VFS, "(cached)\n");
@@ -405,7 +406,19 @@
 
 	p9_debug(P9_DEBUG_VFS, "fid %d\n", fid->fid);
 
-	if (fid->mode & (P9L_DIRECT | P9L_NOWRITECACHE))
+	/*
+	 * CONFIG_WASM: each user process has its OWN WebAssembly.Memory,
+	 * distinct from the kernel's. Unbuffered/direct I/O pins the user
+	 * buffer's pages (netfs_extract_user_iter -> iov_iter_extract_pages)
+	 * and copies them in kernel space -- impossible when the bytes live in
+	 * a separate Memory the kernel cannot address: the pin resolves the
+	 * shared kernel Memory at the user offset, so the write lands as zeros.
+	 * Force the cached/buffered path, whose copy flows through the
+	 * host-bridge copy_from_user choke point. Mirrors the cache=loose read
+	 * mounts (bootstrap.nix).
+	 */
+	if (!IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_WASM) &&
+	    (fid->mode & (P9L_DIRECT | P9L_NOWRITECACHE)))
 		return netfs_unbuffered_write_iter(iocb, from);
 
 	p9_debug(P9_DEBUG_CACHE, "(cached)\n");
